  "prompt": "Are maps of New York City free?",
  "response": "Yes, maps of New York City are generally available for free. There are several sources where you can obtain free maps:\n\n1. **Online Maps and Apps**: Websites like Google Maps, Apple Maps, and OpenStreetMap provide detailed, free maps of New York City. These platforms also offer features like directions and traffic updates.\n\n2. **City Websites and Apps**: The official NYC government website and related tourism websites often offer free digital maps, including subway maps, bus maps, and tourist attraction maps.\n\n3. **Public Transportation Maps**: The Metropolitan Transportation Authority (MTA) provides free maps of its subway and bus systems. These maps can be accessed online or obtained at subway stations.\n\n4. **Visitor Centers**: If you're visiting New York City, you can find free physical maps at visitor centers, major transportation hubs, and some hotels.\n\n5. **Libraries**: Public libraries may offer free maps and guides as part of their visitor information sections.\n\nThese resources should help you navigate the city without any cost.",
